      <h2>About me</h2>

      <p>My name is Rick Waalders and I am a designer with an engineering background. I finished a computer science degree to become a developer, but the design part of building a product has always been my biggest passion. I love finding that sweet spot of applications that aren't just looking great, but are also very easy to use.</p>

      <p>I post design work and interact with other designers on <a href="http://dribbble.com/rickwaalders">Dribbble</a>. You can also find me on <a href="http://twitter.com/rickwaalders">Twitter</a> or contact me through <a href="mailto:rwaalders@gmail.com">email</a>.</p>

      <p>As a developer, I've built applications in Objective-C, C#, PHP and of course Javascript, HTML and CSS. Every once in a while I write some Ruby too.</p>


      <blockquote class="quote">Simplicity is about subtracting the obvious, and adding the meaningful.
